–26).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="442F1D50C1317E4DFF661472FF169AC0" blockId="24.[151,1437,594,1700]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Types.—According to 
<bibRefCitation id="200160A1C1317E4DFE501472FDA49A48" author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[417,611,594,620]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="110 - 116" refId="ref56470" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1930) Familia Belostomidae, generos y especies para la Argentina. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 3, 110 - 116." type="journal article" year="1930">De Carlo (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="200160A1C1317E4DFD9F1472FCD79A48" author="Lauck, D. R." box="[622,784,594,620]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="34 - 81" refId="ref58101" refString="Lauck, D. R. (1962) A monograph of the genus Belostoma (Hemiptera) Part I. Introduction to B. dentatum and subspinosum groups. Bulletin of the Chicago Academy of Sciences, 11 (3), 34 - 81." type="journal article" year="1962">Lauck (1962)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="200160A1C1317E4DFCBD1472FBC09A48" author="Schnack, J. A." box="[844,1031,594,620]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref59891" refString="Schnack, J. A. (1976) Los Belostomatidae de la Republica Argentina (Hemiptera). In: Ringuelet, R. A. (Ed), Fauna de Agua Dulce de la Republica Argentina, volume 35, Fasciculo 1, Fecic, Buenos Aires, 1 - 66." type="book chapter" year="1976">Schnack (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="839066D3C1317E4DFBE21472FB459A4F" authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1930" box="[1043,1154,594,619]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dallasi">
<emphasis id="76E4C142C1317E4DFBE21472FB459A4F" box="[1043,1154,594,619]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">B. dallasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a male 
<typeStatus id="9B2BA3F2C1317E4DFF1C145AFE939AB0" box="[237,340,634,660]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
and a female 
<typeStatus id="9B2BA3F2C1317E4DFE0C145AFDA59AB0" box="[509,610,634,660]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">paratype</typeStatus>
[locality not mentioned] deposited in MLPA, and on 
<typeStatus id="9B2BA3F2C1317E4DFB2E145AFA889AB0" box="[1247,1359,634,660]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">paratypes</typeStatus>
(
<collectingRegion id="8654D3B2C1317E4DFA91145AFEC59A98" country="Argentina" name="Salta" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Salta Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3C875DC0C1317E4DFEFE1482FE419A98" box="[271,390,674,700]" name="Argentina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Argentina</collectingCountry>
) in MACN, and Lizer’s and Trelles’ collections. These specimens have not been examined.
</paragraph>
